   - "also the comment icon is flickering when i hove on it, i cant click it"

7. Pending Tasks:
   - Fix the flickering badge issue in ParagraphCommentLayer — the badge needs to be always rendered in the DOM (not conditionally mounted/unmounted) and use CSS visibility/opacity to show/hide, so hover transitions are smooth and clickable
   - User still needs to run the SQL migration in Supabase SQL Editor to add the FK constraint

8. Current Work:
   The user reported "also the comment icon is flickering when i hove on it, i cant click it". I had just read the current `ParagraphCommentLayer.jsx` file to investigate. The root cause is that the component conditionally renders badge anchors (`if (!isHovered && !hasComments) return null`) which causes mount/unmount cycles. The debounce timer approach (150ms) is insufficient because React's re-render from `setHoveredIndex(null)` unmounts the badge DOM node before the timer can be cancelled by a badge mouseenter.

